Bootstrap: docker
From: python:3.10-slim-bookworm

%labels
    Maintainer BrainBeam
    Description Singularity/Apptainer build of the BrainBeam image-processing pipeline, mirroring the repository's Dockerfile for use on HPC/SLURM clusters where Docker itself is unavailable.

%post
    set -e
    export DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
    apt-get update
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        bash \
        build-essential \
        ca-certificates \
        pkg-config \
        libblosc-dev \
        libblosc1 \
        libgl1 \
        libglib2.0-0 \
        libhdf5-dev \
        libjpeg62-turbo \
        libjpeg62-turbo-dev \
        liblz4-1 \
        liblz4-dev \
        libopenjp2-7 \
        libopenjp2-7-dev \
        libsnappy-dev \
        libsnappy1v5 \
        libtiff-dev \
        libtiff6 \
        libxml2 \
        libxml2-dev \
        libxslt1-dev \
        libxslt1.1 \
        libzstd-dev \
        libzstd1 \
        tk \
        zlib1g \
        zlib1g-dev
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    mkdir -p /opt/brainbeam
    cp -a /tmp/brainbeam_src/. /opt/brainbeam/
    rm -rf /tmp/brainbeam_src
    cd /opt/brainbeam

    python -c "from pathlib import Path; p=Path('requirements.txt'); data=p.read_bytes(); text=data.decode('utf-16le') if b'\x00' in data[:256] else data.decode('utf-8-sig'); lines=[line.strip() for line in text.splitlines() if line.strip() and not line.lstrip().startswith('#')]; Path('requirements.docker.txt').write_text('\n'.join(lines) + '\n', encoding='utf-8')"
    python -m pip install --upgrade pip setuptools wheel
    python -m pip install -r requirements.docker.txt
    python -m pip install customtkinter
    python -m pip install --no-deps .
    rm -f requirements.docker.txt

%files
    . /tmp/brainbeam_src

%environment
    export PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE=1
    export PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1
    export PIP_NO_CACHE_DIR=1

%runscript
    exec /bin/bash "$@"

%help
    Singularity/Apptainer build of BrainBeam for use on HPC/SLURM clusters.

    Build (on a machine/node where you have fakeroot or sudo access, e.g. a
    build/login node with --fakeroot enabled, NOT typically a compute node):
        bash build_singularity.sh
        # or directly:
        singularity build --fakeroot brainbeam.sif Singularity.def

    Use on the cluster (no root needed to run, only to build):
        singularity exec --bind /path/to/scratch:/data brainbeam.sif \
            python /opt/brainbeam/BrainBeam/gui/BrainBeamCLI.py --help

    Or drop into an interactive shell inside the image:
        singularity shell --bind /path/to/scratch:/data brainbeam.sif

    Note: SLURM submission/orchestration scripts (the *_spinup.sh files and
    pipeline_spinup.sh) call sbatch directly and are meant to run natively
    on the cluster, not inside the container. Use this image for running
    individual pipeline stages reproducibly inside an sbatch job step, e.g.
    by replacing a script's "python foo.py" call with
    "singularity exec brainbeam.sif python foo.py".
